# 9\. Data Management Requirements

## 9.1 Data Classification

| **Classification** | **Description**                                | **Handling Requirements**              |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Public             | Open data, derived products for public release | No special handling required           |
| Internal           | Commercial imagery, operational telemetry      | Access control, encryption at rest     |
| Confidential       | High-resolution imagery, intelligence products | Strict RBAC, audit logging, encryption |
| Restricted         | Export-controlled, defense-related data        | ITAR/EAR compliance, isolated systems  |

## 9.2 Data Retention

- Raw satellite imagery: 7 years minimum, archive tier after 1 year
- Processed products: 5 years, regenerable from raw data
- Satellite telemetry: Indefinite retention with compression after 90 days
- Intelligence reports: 10 years with annual review
- Audit logs: 7 years in tamper-evident storage

# 10\. Glossary

| **Term** | **Definition**                                                               |
